caption: Nice Food  thank you
Great food and friendly workers! Favorite spot for food that screams NOLA!!
Seriously the best po boy I've had in years.  And do yourself a favor...get the homemade banana pudding.  It's pure joy.
Best shrimp po boy I've had outside of New Orleans
First time trying gumbo. Seafood gumbo was great. Cleaned the place up and ate everything. Shrimp poboy was goo. Fun for sure. Soft bread, crispy outside.
Food & drinks were amazing. Staff was very nice.

I was walking back to work from lunch, I see a sign LIMITED BEIGNETS.. I go in,  place an order with Lucky who was very nice. OMG... They were amazing! took me back to Cafe Du Monde in NOLA. I can not wait to try  the actual food.

We had not visited Gumbo Bros in a while.  We were so looking forward to their seafood gumbo and catfish sandwich!!  The catfish sandwich was great!!  Crunchy and tasty as always.  The seafood gumbo was VERY disappointing.  The rice was a mushy lump and the shrimps were NOT fresh.  They were almost inedible, like biting into a piece of dough, it had no shrimp characteristic!!  Hope that this was an aberration. 😡😡

Thinking of having a Gumbo since it’s Mardi Gras. Google a bit, and the place showed up. The Seafood Gumbo is good, and they’re very generous on the shrimps! I ordered a pickup and don’t need to wait long. Staff is friendly.
Fast delivery and great food!

The closest you'll get to true Louisiana food.  Nothing in this city comes close.  I am In New Orleans at least 4 times a year and my wife is originally from New Orleans and there is no place she has approved of until she came to Gumbo Bros.  She validates their authenticity
Best Gumbo in NY

Ordered the catfish basket to go. It was ready and waiting when I arrived. Generous portion of fish. Gorgeous crust. Huge serving of fries. Man... that sauce, yum. I inhaled everything when I got home. I'm full but I wish I'd had a cup of gumbo as well. Next time!
I found my new spot,

All perfectly prepared. I would definitely eat there again and probably order the chicken fry bread sandwich. The other reason for only 4 stars is that they had plastic silver ware, but were out of forks! So I had to eat my eggs and hash browns with a spoon. Also the napkins were the roll of paper towels.

cajun food and service at this location is super good. Excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. The service was friendly and observant. Prices were reasonable. Atmosphere is like a restaurant in Fort Worth I loved.

DELICIOUS and the Thai food is pretty good, but nothing special. The Thai menu was large, but I was told that they were out of or no longer carried a number of items. I ordered basil chicken because the menu listed it as using ground meat, my preference, but it was served with sliced meat instead. It was fine
Had the gumbo soup and the Catfish po boy.. The Gumbo soup was a bit to spicy for me and the Po boy was good but could have been more meaty. For the price I would not recommend!

After years wishing to be there, finally I had the time. I go inside to order and the woman at the register was like a robot. How can I help you? She said. I told her about how much my cravings were for Their food... not a smile. Charged me for the food and that was it The place is beautiful decorated and I am sure the owners are not like that, just employees behave like that on an hourly salary. And after visiting New Orleans I am sure that’s not the vibe neither. Food is overpriced, shrimp gumbo was basically a black pepper tea, thin and very spicy. There was absolutely no roux on that soup. And for $25 +tax+tips it wasn’t worth it.
Such great cajun food and the vibe is very reminiscent of NOLA! The catfish gumbo is my go to but also love everything else I’ve tried!

The steak entree was a generous portion and delicious, and my friend raved about her fish entree. The chocolate sorbet from Piety Desire Chocolates was a showstopper and a perfect ending. My DH got the pecan pie which is always amazing.
The food there is delicious! My favorite meal is the cajun spicy gumbo, shrimp Po' boy and the banana pudding. I recommend it.
One of my top spots for delicious cajun food. I love this place, great food & service. Really nothing but enjoyable experiences here, I'll be back. They have a lot of good reviews for a reason.
Cajun food, delicious. Came in on a Weds. Really nothing but great experiences here, so I will be back. The bill was average for the menu. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I loved.

This is a perfect new Orleans shrimp poboy. I lived in New Orleans for 8 years and ate poboys all over. This is as good as it gets. The bread is right. The shrimp are generous and tasty and good sized. A little mayo and a little pickle. What else can you ask for?
Authentic, NOLA po-boys and friendly staff
Cajun food and the feeling here is great. i had a brother come into town and asked me to take him back here. prices that won't shock you.
Drove a long way for some gumbo. Totally worth it.
Great food!!  The catfish,  one piece instead of pieces,  brought it down to 4!!!
Nice site for tasty cajun food. the food was so savory. looking forward to coming back with my friends. this place has many reviews for a reason.
cajun food... excellent. Excellent spot to spend time alone or talk business. Looking forward to coming back with my relatives. It has a good feel to it.

I ordered from this place tonight with my husband. I’ve had their food many times before but this time compelled me to write a review- this place is bomb AF their food is so delicious and satisfying. I have never been to NOLA but this definitely has me curious now. I had the chicken po’boy. The chicken was cooked to perfection perfectly seasoned, veggies were fresh, tasty pickles and the dukes mayo/French bread combo is to die for. Thank you!

I've Been Wanting To Try This Place For Along Time. Finally Went Yesterday, Took A Uber All The Way From The Bronx. I Must Say, The Seafood Gumbo & The Chicken Gumbo Is What I Had. Good Amount Of Food. Good Seasoning. Just Hate That The Menu Had Limited Options. Guess Because Of COVID. But I Would Recommend.
Food was hot and good.  Tasty eats. Check it out!
Ausally Miami Florida next location plan this month Miami Florida thanks please this August plan
First, they were incredibly flexible with my reservation so props to them for that.

If u want a rich meal where everything is done well and the service is friendly this is a good stop. The fried chicken is the mainstay and it was well prepared. Everything in the menu is pretty heavy from the creamed corn to the macaroni. Heavy and tasty.
SO GOOD!!! Everything from the atmosphere to the Mac and cheese! Highly recommend coming here and trying the Chicken and the Mac and cheese! Can't wait to come back and try other items on the menu.

This place is cool, love the food above all else especially the fried chicken!  But also everything about it. It's very much a southern experience, from the chicken to the bucket to the drinks, it's well thought out!

Easy over the phone reservations made a few days in advance. The four of us arrived on time and were quickly led to a nice faux leather booth. While we peruse the menus, we were greeted with four tiny cornbread muffins and yummy herb butter. Delish!
Food was pretty good, we order a bucket of chicken and it came with 2 sides. Chicken was fresh mashed potatoes were good but not a fan of the collard greens.
Best po boy sandwiches downtown. Friendly staff.
Always good food..Always friendly staff.Happy they have survived through CORONA.
Restaurant was cozy, the food was super delicious, great customer service and I had the vegan soup. "Gumbo Z' Herbes'. The food is a little spicy but enjoyable.
Haven't had a po boy this good since the last time I was in New Orleans. Batter was well seasoned, the rémoulade was on point and the bread perfect. Next time I'm gonna try the debris...

I got the honey chicken po boy and the shrimp and crab meat gumbo! Firstly I wanna say that the po boy was good but everyone else that ordered after me there sandwiches seemed to be a lot heartier than mines. Either way it still wasnt bad.i gave it a 3 because with all the ingredients that was in the gumbo it had absolutely no taste what so ever! It was very spicy but was very tasteless. I just expected so much more. I felt robbed of my first keto cheat! That was totally not worth me being kicked out of ketosis.
Great potential.  No flavor tho....

Great po boys and New Orleans authenticity. Today is Mardi Gras and I’m thinking of going there to celebrate. Roast Beef is my favorite po boy and theirs is good but not as amazing as Parkway Bakery or some other places in NOLA. I can’t put my finger on why and I don’t fault them for it. The good vibes and really tasty gumbo keep me loving this place despite my picky roast beef desires.
Everything here is tasty. The banana pudding is especially scrumptous!

The shrimp and catfish Po' boys are so good. My only complaint is everything else is so spicy, but that's a personal thing. The place is small but quaint. I would definitely recommend it if you are in the neighborhood.
Takes me back to New Orleans!
great place ,shrimp gumbo.
IDK THE GUMBO WAS BITTER ....
The food was amazing and the beers were fantastic...... It was a bit cold and although I did find a hair in my food, I still ate afterwards bcuz it was so tasty
The food here is legitimately good. But not good enough for the prices they charge and the quantities of food received. You'll pay $6 for six half-slices of fried green tomato.

UhMazing Food (The Catfish was WOW) and efficient service is the name of their game. The Lil Lady behind the counter was on it with walk'ins, takeout and several UBER Eats deliveries. I saw every kinda person eat in an hour and they all finished their food!
Worth the wait. Delicious food and staff very accommodating in answering all questions and making sure your order is just right.
Cool little take out joint that the flavors are anything but little. Super Po' boys and Jambalaya, Excellent!!!
Food is really good, especially the Gumbo.
The vegan gumbo hair was very good

Great po boys - our go to has been the catfish, but the hot honey chicken is also juicy and delicious.  The seafood gumbo teems with seafood, including large shrimp and blue crab.  The fried green tomatoes come with a great dipping sauce, a creamy bit of tang, a bit of spice.

I loved their fried catfish poboy, the seafood gumbo, and beignets. I loved every bite of the breading on the catfish and the sauce in the sandwich. Things tasted freshly made and well spiced. I am definitely going to come back again to try more poboys and the pecan pie.
Delicious took my fam. Ordered po'boys, fried green tomatoes and gumbo
As close to NOLA as you can get in NY
Put good food... bith the catfish and the gumbo is seasoned great... kind of pricey, but worth the money... And they make it to your liking...
Great staff and selections!
(Translated by Google) A true southern diner in manhattan, more than fair prices and excellent quality  (Original) Una vera tavola calda del sud a manhattan, prezzi più che onesti ed ottima qualità
It's the best dadgum stew I ever have eaten.

Should’ve known not to choose a place from the pictures they advertise... I purchased the hot honey fried chicken pow boy and was just so disappointed.. the chicken wasn’t even crunchy and hardly had any taste, all I can really taste was the mayonnaise and lettuce.. Popeyes, Chick-Fil-A and pretty much every fast food chicken sandwich I ever had was better than this.

We absolutely love it at The Gumbo Bros. The owners, Adam & Clay are great guys doing all the dishes right. My favorites are the Po-boys and Gumbo, which both take me right back home to NOLA. Also, they’ve been really investing in the beer menu lately and it’s rocking. Equally great for dining in & takeout / delivery.

Been looking around for a good bowl of gumbo for quite some time as I hadn't had one in years. Found out about the Gumbo Bros and went for it.  Loved the seafood gumbo. It's got just the right amount of heat such that it works very well with the shrimp and crabmeat. Amazing flavor such that I didn't need to add any hot sauce to it and would definitely have again.  Gonna come back to try them Po'Boys next time I swing by, although that seafood gumbo is tempting to have again. Definitely know where I'm getting my gumbo fix from now on.
Great food and atmosphere. Gumbo is dark and smokey and the sandwiches are straight outta the LA bayou (in a good way)
Delicious beignets
Good Gumbo
Best gumbo in New York.
Friendly and easy-going vibe with excellent food. Great place to work! Staff is well-treated. Everyone is kind and gets along. Highly recommend for your next dinning experience
Great catfish po' boy
Authentic new orlean food and $5 happy hour beer weekend. Great place to watch the new orleans game.

Sooooooo disappointed. I've gotten shrimp po boys from this place a few times and I've never received a po boy quite like the one I have today. It looks like they ran out of shrimp and fresh bread when they got to my order. Super disappointed
Delish, and filling
Not only does this place have good food, the service is true"southern hospitality." Has a big clean bathroom too.
Very disappointed. After a long wait, the rice in our gumbos was still barely cooked. The sausage & chicken was so little that I thought I was eating some rice soup. Will not recommend to anyone.
Paid 14$ got watery gumbo. Ordered the death gumbo, which has shrimp, chicken, sausage. Had 5 pieces of shrimp 2 bits of sausage and the chicken was untracable.
They are really awesome.

Finally stopped after work one night. I ordered the sausage gumbo to take out. It was amazing. A little heat and lots of flavor that lasted after the last spoonful. Can't wait to try a po'boy and a beignet. They also sell Other Half beer.
Love the food here! Vegetarian friendly menu
Always a killer meal. The sausage gumbo is incredible. My go to is an Abita, a Po Boy, and some gumbo. Can't go wrong here.
The shrimps on the PoBoy were tough and over cooked have eaten there many times first time this has happened
Fantastic establishment with unbelievably delicious food. If I could get their gumbo injectors into my veins, I’d do it.
The food is great, tasty, flavorful, filling. Great lunch deal. But... what I really want to know is, where can I find that Lil Wayne portrait in the shop right about the kitchen entrance?
Loved the vegan and vegetarian options + great service and beer choices for a southern feel.
Their fried shrimp po'boy is everything 😋
DELICIOUS!!! SIMPLY DELIGHTFUL.
I've eaten there several times not excellent pretty good good place to go not a bad atmosphere food is pretty good something quick and fast

Love it! Been a regular of Gumbo Bros since their days at Urban Eats in Herald Square & Columbus Circle! The gumbos (seafood, chicken/sausage, And vegetarian) are ALL amazing! Alllllll of their PO Boys are delicious too! Oh and those delicious beignets are a sinfully good dessert!  I was SO excited to visit the Gumbo Bros' new brick & mortar location, and it does not disappoint!  The place is cosy, with a brick wall on one side, complete with pics and descriptions of their 2 featured foods: Gumbo ("a big bowl of southern comfort") and Po'Boys ("the best sandwich you'll ever scarf").  They also have regular beer, root beer, and cold brew on tap.  For the layout: There are 3 tables (2 tall, for standing/stools; and one short, with regular chairs) lining a red wall on the left side. You order and pay up front at the back, with a peek-view of the kitchen (where they work their magic!).  If you're lucky enough to meet the owners, they are so so nice too, and very open and friendly!  (I'm also hoping for a return of the Rabbit Stew they featured once during their days at Urban Bites!)  Either way though, The Gumbo Bros is Definitely worth a special trip from Manhattan for, and that's saying a lot!!
I hope I can remember to go back to this place the next time I'm in Brooklyn!
These brothers  got Brooklyn
Delicious and friendly. Love the Gumbo
Yummy gumbo

When I first from this place the food didn't really speak to me. But a year later I went back with a few friends and try they're unbelievably good crawfish. I've also tried a few other things and I'm sold.

As close as New Orleans authentic as your gonna get in NYC. Everything is delicious.

Good food my catfish sandwich was real tastey my seafood gumbo was also tastey but a bit to spicey whereas I cldnt enjoy it my boyfriend also enjoyed his oyster pooboy he said he thinks thet shucked it on spot and my ginger ale was so good you actually taste the ginger

I was pretty disappointed with my experience. Staff is friendly and nice, place has a good vibe to it.  I got their signature pork po boy sandwich. Well that thing was very small and barely had pork. It would have been fine if it had not been priced $16. Don't trust their marketing pictures. It did taste good though.
Gumbo is dope
It's not the same as being in New Orleans, but it's pretty damn close.

I don’t really know how to rate this place because I only tried the vegan gumbo . But other things on the site look delicious in photo like the shrimp po boy . Anyhow I got a sample of the vegan gumbo and my co worker tried the seafood gumbo. It was very watery and had a background taste to it . We did not order anything we just left after traveling from Staten Island to get here. The inside is very nice and has a few tables for sitting and a picnic table.

It was a really fantastic cup of gumbo but being from New Orleans myself I really expected the poboy to have more flavor. The counter staff was a little dismissive and seemed annoyed when I asked her to review my order before charging me. But the gumbo really was delicious, just like my dad used to make.
Best kept secret. A Brooklyn gem. Their crawfish boil is pricey and worth every dollar! Tried it once after that purchased 2 at a time.
Love it! The food is authentically Cajun and delicious. And I should know because I'm Cajun. Geaux here!
Delicious po-boy shrimp sandwiches and friendly staff

I didn't have to wait when I came. There happened to be an empty table for 2 right when I got there. There's a sign in list that you'll miss because it's positioned on the wall where people stand to wait. (On the right when you walk in at
Definitely will be back!

(Translated by Google) A cool pub in Brooklyn, mainly locals eat here. I recommend a shrimp sandwich and Gumbo soup. Moderate prices.  (Original) Fajna knajpka na Brooklynie,  jedzą tu głównie miejscowi. Polecam kanapkę z krewetkami i zupę Gumbo.  Ceny umiarkowane.
My preferred place for delicious Cajun food. i look forward to a return visit. prices were good for how much you get.
cajun food and the scene at this place is great. The service was very sociable and kind. It has a great interior.
Because of their pics they have on the walls of rap icons and I believe country music stars. It just gives you a feeling that everyone is welcomed and the staff are very welcoming also

NYC’s most legit taste of Louisiana it is not. Were you guys like banking on people never having been to NOLA and that they won’t recognize good? ... I’ve been to New Orleans and had several delicious gumbos and have held my own in making some. But when I saw there was an actual restaurant in NY I was excited to try. I spend $30 on a po’ Boy, a cup of gumbo and beignets. Fine - a bit costly but this is New York. NOT WORTH IT AT ALL. The gumbo tasted like a burnt Marsala. Heavy on the bay leaf and cayenne. No flavor just spice (not spicy) and bay leaf. Over-all bitter and not enjoyable. The rice inside was cold and the gumbo itself thick.  You guys did me dirty with the po’boy and gave me the tops of unripe tomato’s. You could hear a thud as I pulled them from the sandwich (as they were inedible) and dropped them onto the tray. The fish was fried in what could at best be compared to fish fry that you buy at the supermarket. IThe beignets tasted like zepolis found at a pizza shop. I did not complete one dish. All lack luster and kind of nasty. One star because the man behind the counter was polite. Please don’t go here.

This is 2 blocks from my job and I been wanting to try it. Finally went for it and got the roast beef po boy. Wow! It's delicious. Tendered sliced/shredded beef with perfect amount of lettuce, tomato, pickles and mayo. That gravy is amazing. The bread was on point. Going to have to get the rice and gravy next time just to let that gravy shine. Will for sure be trying other items on the menu. If you been wanting to try, just do it. You won't be disappointed.
I would give them zero stars. Waited 30 min after I ordered and was told they forgot to make it.
Po boys,gumbo and beer a hidden little gem. Food is sooo tasty and not to pricey
Real good food but kinda pricey for the portion size
Consistent quality. Reasonable prices. Good size portions.
Limited menu and a small environment but very cute!

Cozy, rustic, very quaint. Had the Alabama catfish and fried tomatoes. GF had the gumbo, collards and red beans & rice. My baby doesn't care too much for spicy food, but I love it!! The collards were not to my liking, too spicy and I tasted vinegar. Rice & beans was delicious. The poh boi was to die for. The fried tomatoes I felt was a tad to spicy. I guess to give it a little something. I'm southern. Nobody at home makes it that spicy. I LOVED THE NATURAL SODA. If you don't do anything else. You gotta try it. Food was over priced, spicy were it wasn't necessary and the collards were not to my liking. Overall not bad.
To expensive for what get

I found them and came fro Harlem just to try and see for myself. The place is inviting and open.  I had the sausage and shrimp gumbo cup. I'm a greedy person and cup is deep so its more than enough especially if you pair it with the sandwich.  Gumbo was good and filling. Shrimp po'boy had lots of shrimp and nice warmed bread.  The boudin balls were soooooo good. Highly underrated. They are huge and the taste is not lacking at all.  It's a must try. P.s. the had one of my face hot sauce crystal
The sides are never consistent on what you pay for, and  I didn't like the batter on the catfish póboy.
Amazing food, rare find

I went there on day of Mardi Gras. I had Mardi Gras bock beer, sausage gumbo and fried green tomatoes. They were very good. The place is very small and may be not the place to hang out for long hours. The traffic is quite quick so even if it's packed, you'll find a seat in 10~15 minutes.

Great authentic, right spicey, New Orleans Cajun food at a right, decent price. Various types of Gumbo, Po'Boys and soups. Small cup size good for one and a Bowl is good for two or take home,Best kept secret in NYC but not for long. Not much room for eat-in but some seating. They need a bigger place!!!!!
Not bad for a quick bite. Location is good and the interior is nice. Still, not quite the authentic cajun place I was hoping for. Flavors are... Close, just not quite right.

Small and Quant location where you can get great louisiana style foods and have a beer and watch TV. Shrimp Poboys are amazing! Seafood gumbo amazing with great spices. Id recommend anytime. Parking in area is a bit tough but parking lots around as well. Enjoy

Having lived in the Gumbo Belt I wasn’t expecting to have authentic Cajun food in Brooklyn, but man was I happy to be proved wrong. This place needs to be on your list of hole-in-the-wall restaurants to visit while in New York. The staff was all so nice and the food was out of this world. I can’t wait to go back on my next visit.
Delicious shrimp gumbo soup and the banana pudding was one of the best I've ever had.

So I was looking for something different and saw the reviews so thought I would give it a try.  I went in with no expectations.  My review is based upon both going to college in new Orleans  and working in southern Louisiana so have had my fair share of cajun food. Cute place.  Counter service but that is OK it is gumbo and po-boys.  I ordered a cup of seafood gumbo, a shrimp po-boy, and a beer. The good:  lots of shrimp in both dishes.  The shrimp was good and tender. Unfortunately the good stopped there.  The bad: the gumbo was bitter, appeared to only have shrimp, little too thick, and too many bay leaves.  Seafood gumbo is a kitchen sink kind of dish for seafood but that adds the flavor.  It was bland otherwise and you should not be able to stand your spoon up in it. The po-boy was dry.  Where was the rich, tangy remoulade.  The French bread was good though. Look, wish them all the luck but need some spice.
Solid gumbo, abita root beer, other half ipa, and surprisingly a really good chicken sandwich!

I am a huge fan of po'boys.  My wife is from New Orleans and I've been fortunate to try a variety of them every time we've gone to NOLA.  I was excited to try Gumbo Bros and got a Shrimp Po'Boy, dressed.  The flavor was fine and there were a good number of shrimp, but my sandwich fell apart almost immediately and the batter on the shrimp kept coming off as well.  Service was friendly but not sure I'd return.
Gumbo and service is great. Pretty chill space.
Solid food. Gumbo had to much heat for me.  I couldn't handle the spiciness of it.
The food is excellent here!

Pretty good place to swing by for a quick meal to catch. The po'boys are nice and freshly prepared; although the seafood gumbo contained "mushy" shrimp that didn't offer a delightful texture. While thick in consistency and full of fillings, it was also overseasoned (in my opinion). Nice decor space reminscent of New Orleans.
Great Food, Dope Atmosphere.

Haven't had Gumbo this good since visiting New Orleans!  The Seafood Gumbo was Hearty, Spicy, Delicious, & Fresh!  I went back again 2 days later!
Best poboys and Gumbo in NYC, no question.
Love this place with amazing poboys and gumbo! Straight from New Orleans!
Soulful smell
Huge fan for everything NOLA , gumbo bros don't disappoint, plus everything is made or shipped from the gulf. It's on Atlantic Ave and close to Trader Joe's
The gumbo is amazing and so is the fried green tomatoes
My wife grew up on the Bayou. She says this is a good as her family's cooking back home. Amazing po' boys, red beans & rice, Gumbo and if you're lucky - they do a crawfish bowl occasionally.
Food tastes like 100% down south dinner

I though we were going to have Jerk Chicken but what this restaurant serves is Cajun Chicken. How silly I was! However it was a good mistake! We had a great lunch there - the food,the drink, the service and the atmosphere are superb!
Gotta do the gumbo and shrimp po' boy! Awesome all the way around!
Really good chicken and sausage gumbo, root beer is good too!
Excellent!
Good experience
As good a po'boy as you can get outside of the south. Very authentic. Always friendly service and atmosphere!
Ordered a seafood gumbo and it's very flavorful, would be better if it's less salty or came with more rice to neutralize it.
Great service! I got the hot honey chicken po' boy & commented to a friend that I would've liked more of th3 hot honey, and one of the servers overheard & brought me some.

I had the seafood gumbo and half of a shrimp sandwich. This is the best gumbo in NYC. Couldn’t help my self and returned to this place for lunch for a second day in a row. Full portion of gumbo and a half sandwich is $20, but it’s worth every penny. They have lunch specials that come with a small gumbo and half sandwich for around $14.
Authentic adoption from the cajun to brooklynites... My lunch was nice half gumbo and half sandwich option not in the menu.
Excellent po boys and gumbo. Zapps and Crystal on premise as well. Hey Gumbo Bro’s please make a muffuletta!
Awesome

Excellent! Great service and atmosphere too!
not what i expected clean small but not what i expected
The Gumbo Bros never fails! I've been several times and I try something new each time and everything is an absolute hit!
They have a Louisianan beers on tap like Purple Haze, great Gumbo and this place has a whole in the wall feel.  Come around the Atlantic Antic Festival for some Alligator Gumbo!
Just two words: Excellent gumbo!

I was here for an intimate YE and the Gumbo Bros did it well! I've never had this gumbo I've heard so much about so I was eager to try.  I'll list what I ate in the order I ate it:  A. Boudin Balls which I renamed rice balls were spicy and fall apart juicy. I was shocked I enjoyed this so much because I'm not a spicy eater. After I had everything else I even had one more balls they were so good. One more balls, hahahaha, anyway I digress.  B. Hot honey fried chicken (sandwich). Hot, crispy and so so tasty. Like mummy made them herself tasty.  C. Seafood z'herbs gumbo was different. Like I said it was my first time trying...give me some time.  D. The fried green tomatoes with the accompanying dip was a savory, delish treat!  E. Chicken and sausage gumbo. Now by this time I'm super full and eating out of spite. I kid you not. I'm not registering what's happening in my mouth and stomach.  F. The Peachy pig poboy or (pulled pork sandwiche) so so tender and juicy.  G. Braised (collard) greens I found extremely tart.  H. That banana pudding! My first. You've got to get to The Gumbo Bros and try yourself! You MUST!  I. The New Orleans tunes playing in the background, so cool! Dem horns!  The Gumbo Bros showed us such a wonderful time! Adam, his bro, Kai and the rest of their team worked tirelessly to make sure we wanted for nothing! Platter after platter plus we left a full boat of beer.  Thank you so much to our Peter and Katey for putting together such a wonderful evening! You work hard to keep raising the bar and I for one feel really blessed to be on this food journey with you. Always happy to catch up with my fellow buds.  The End.
Especially the surf and turf Po boy and the desserts are amazing! We often being visitors to NYC here.
Soul warming on a cold day
Took me back to New Orleans 🤩
Cheap Cajun but tasty
This place is amazing. Had the seafood gumbo and it was a real piece of new Orleans in Brooklyn!
Real real good.

Had both the gumbo and red beans and rice and I will say this is some of the best Cajun food I’ve had outside of my own family’s cooking. Seasoning and ingredients are perfect, I’m full but want to eat more.  This is a staple restaurant for me in Brooklyn, don’t miss out.
Good tasting fish sandwich.

Fun, small space with great food. We got the gumbo which was perfectly spicy (just needed a little salt) and one of the po boys. A little pricey but the portion sizes and taste was worth it!

Came here after fasting for my yearly physical. Usually under this circumstance I could eat frozen liver and find it delicious, but this food was such a let down, I'm writing a review to keep from crying! The lunch special of half a fried shrimp po' boy and a small seafood gumbo for $14 was so alluring. I treated myself to a sweet and fizzy root beer from the tap (they also had beer), put $2 in the jar since they bring the food to your table, and sat down, enjoying the soulful and hip music, excited for some comfort food. When the tray was placed, I immediately was struck by the texture/sheen of the gumbo - appearing to be less-than-hot and not well incorporated.  I hate to sound snooty, but if you cook, you know what it looks when the pot is not yet done. The shrimp in the gumbo was overcooked, like something that was too chewy, and made to cook longer to re-soften. Unfortunately, whatever flavors were ever in the shrimp were lost in the base, which tasted strongly of bitter pepper skin and celery. The po'boy was slightly better: lettuce and tomato were fresh and brightly colored, and the bread was decent. Again, the shrimp part was wrong: cajun season was too light, and breading mostly salty, the shrimp inside tasted pre-boiled and therefore not very much like fresh shrimp. If I had not been fasting for the last 15 hours, I might have walked out with my dignity, but I worked through the sandwich and most of the gumbo. Then I spent the rest of the day with that lump-in-esophagus feeling you get when you don't salivate enough to properly moisten and digest food, because the food was just not done well.
I had the lunch special--1/2 Shrimp Po'boy with a cup of seafood gumbo!! Just the right kick for a blustery day!!!
